    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PartnerDelegate

    public abstract class AbstractPartnerDelegate
extends com.poesys.bs.delegate.AbstractDataDelegate<BsPartner,IPartner,com.poesys.db.pk.SequencePrimaryKey>

    A business delegate that provides an application programming interface for Partner objects and their dependents. You should not modify this class; instead, override or add methods in the class PartnerDelegate, which specializes this class.

    a system that comprises a unit for subscription, authentication, and authorization

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
    See Also:
    PartnerDelegate

      • createPartner

        public BsPartner createPartner(java.math.BigInteger partnerId,
                      java.lang.String name,
                      java.lang.String logoUri,
                      java.lang.String termOfServiceUri)
                        throws com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException

        Create a new Partner with data fields.

        The Partner class has a sequence key; this method generates the sequence for later insertion into the database.

        Parameters:
        partnerId - primary key attribute
        name - the name of the partner system
        logoUri - a URI that returns a logo for the partner
        termOfServiceUri - a URI that returns an array of subscription terms for the partner
        Returns:
        the new Partner object
        Throws:
        com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException - when there is a problem generating the key or creating the object

      • createPartnerPattern

        public BsPartnerPattern createPartnerPattern(BsPartner parent,
                                    java.math.BigInteger partnerId,
                                    java.lang.String sourceUri,
                                    java.lang.String targetUri)
                                      throws com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException
        Create a new PartnerPattern child of Partner with a composite key.
        Parameters:
        parent - the parent of the child object to create
        partnerId - composite super-key attribute that uniquely identifies child combined with child sub-key and any other parent super-keys
        sourceUri - the source URI that the user requests; this is a regular expression that identifies a set of potential URIs in a complete match scenario; this is the original URI that comes into the proxy server
        targetUri - the URI that replaces the complete match on the source URI; this is the URI that identifies the partner server (the proxied URI for the proxy server)
        Returns:
        a new PartnerPattern business layer DTO
        Throws:
        com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException - when a parameter causes a problem

        Create a new SubscriptionTerm child of Partner with a composite key.
        Parameters:
        parent - the parent of the child object to create
        partnerId - composite super-key attribute that uniquely identifies child combined with child sub-key and any other parent super-keys
        period - the period of time for which a subscription allows access to a partner system
        price - the price for a subscription for this term
        groupDiscountPercentage - the discount for this term for a group subscription expressed as a decimal number with 2 significant digits
        description - text describing the term suitable for display in the user interface, such as "Annual ($199 USD)" for a 365-day term priced at $199

        public BsSubscriptionTransaction createSubscriptionTransaction(BsPartner parent,
                                                      java.math.BigInteger partnerId,
                                                      java.math.BigInteger partyId,
                                                      java.math.BigInteger transactionNo,
                                                      java.sql.Timestamp transactionDate,
                                                      java.sql.Timestamp startDate,
                                                      java.sql.Timestamp endDate,
                                                      java.lang.String transactionType,
                                                      java.util.UUID activationCodeId)
                                                        throws com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException
        Create a new SubscriptionTransaction child of Partner with a composite key.
        Parameters:
        parent - the parent of the child object to create
        partnerId - composite super-key attribute that uniquely identifies child combined with child sub-key and any other parent super-keys
        partyId - composite super-key attribute that uniquely identifies child combined with child sub-key and any other parent super-keys
        transactionNo - the identifying transaction number within the subscription that uniquely identifies the transaction along with the subscription key
        transactionDate - the date and time of the transaction
        startDate - at the time of the transaction, the date at which the subscription commences
        endDate - at the time of the transaction, the date at which the subscription ends
        transactionType - the kind of transaction: Initial, Renewal, Refund
        activationCodeId - foreign key used by setter to query associated object
        Returns:
        a new SubscriptionTransaction business layer DTO
        Throws:
        com.poesys.bs.delegate.DelegateException - when a parameter causes a problem

        Create a new Subscription association class child of Partner with an association key. This class links the input objects.
        Parameters:
        subscribedPartnersObject - associated Partner object (part of the key)
        subscribersObject - associated Party object (part of the key)
        partnerId - Attribute that is part of the association key
        partyId - Attribute that is part of the association key
        startDate - the date and time at which the subscription commences; if this is in the future, the subscription is not yet in effect
        endDate - the date and time at which the subscription ends
        subscriptionId - an alternate single-number identifier for the subscription
        Returns:
